cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.NI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the practical implementation of a secret key agreement protocol for wireless channels, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with security and privacy, which suggests categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). The use of wireless channels suggests categories such as cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
